Dear Hampton School District School Community,

Our next School Board Meeting will be held on Tuesday, August 11th, 2020 at 4:00 pm. This school board meeting will be held at the town hall and will be able to be viewed live on Channel 22 in town or live online at http://trms-vod.hamptonnh.gov/CablecastPublicSite/watch/3?channel=1. We are asking due to limitation in space that participation by the Hampton community happen by calling the conference phone number 1-857-444-0744 and use the code 156034. We also ask that you mute your phone line until it is time for public comment and you wish to say something. Do note that live participation is about 20-30 seconds delayed while stream online as compare to watching on television.

post_text:
Hampton Arts Network is pleased to announce our 8th annual Youth Impressions Art Show ! This is a juried show for our young Hampton artists in Grades 3 - 8. Each year, the art teachers at Marston School, Hampton Academy, and Sacred Heart School are invited to submit student art. Three HAN artists then serve as jurors to select the pieces for our student show including 1st, 2nd, and 3rd place entries in two Grade level categories--Grades 3 - 5 and Grades 6 - 8. Visitors to the show are invited to vote for People’s Choice winners!
Certificates, cash awards, and ribbons are presented to winners at a special awards presentation evening scheduled for
February 6 at 5:30 p.m.

Youth Impressions Art Show for 2020 opens on January 2 in the Weston Gallery of Lane Memorial Library. Visitors may vote for their favorite entries during the month of January. The
show runs through February 28 and is open to the community during library hours. Come enjoy some fabulous art from these young, creative artists!

post_text:
Comcast has recently made a significant expansion to their Internet Essentials eligibility!

Internet Essentials provides high-speed Internet service for $9.95 a month plus tax; the option to purchase a desktop or laptop computer for $149.99; and access free digital literacy training in print, online, and in person. Individuals may qualify* if they have at least one child who is eligible for the National School Lunch Program, or if they receive public assistance such as housing assistance, Medicaid, SNAP, SSI, and others. Those wishing to apply can call 1-855-8-INTERNET (1-855-846-8376) or visit InternetEssentials.com.

Don't Forget...

Centre School will host a Kindergarten Information Night for incoming 2019-2020 kindergarten on Thursday, April 4th at 6:00 PM in the Centre School gym. The school principal will provide an overview of the kindergarten program. Parents of children who are five years of age by September 30, 2019 and who reside in the town of Hampton are encouraged to register their child for the 2019-2020 kindergarten. If you have questions about the Centre School program or about Kindergarten, please call Principal Tim Lannan at (603) 926-8706 or email the principal at tlannan@sau90.org. Centre School is located at 53 Winnacunnet Rd., Hampton, NH. See the attached picture for additional information!

post_text:
PRESS RELEASE
July 15, 2018
Cornerstone Ceremony

The Hampton School Board is pleased to invite the public to the laying of the cornerstone marker at the site of the new construction at Hampton Academy.
This milestone event will occur on Saturday, July 21st at 10:30 am. The Masonic Lodge of Masons will lead the ritual throughout the ceremony. Through the generous gift from the Mason’s the school district will mark the halfway point in the project.
Members of the Construction Team, Building Committee members and the School Board will be attending the event and participating in the ceremony.
For further information, call the SAU 90 office at 926-4560.

Thank you to Ms. Murphy's fifth grade class from Marston School in Hampton, NH, for making and donating soft, cozy baby blankets for RMCC families!
"Binky Patrol's mission is to bring a caring, loving touch by creating and delivering handmade blankets, 'binkies', to enrich children's lives, and to meet their most baasic needs of warmth, security and comfort."
